# Accidentally vendored site-packages fragments — guard against recurrence of the
# pre-rc.7 "dump site-packages into the source tree" bug (see Version History
# entry for 4.50.0-rc.7 for the purge rationale). Anchored to repo root so a
# legitimate same-named subfolder deeper in the tree is not accidentally hidden.
/Python
/Python.framework/
/webview/
/jsonschema/
/jsonschema_specifications/
/certifi/

# Local adversarial review evidence packets (not shipped)
.adversarial-review/

# Claudexor external-review tooling run artifacts (operator-side, never tracked)
.claudexor/
.review-evidence-iter2/

# GAIA benchmark scratch: the in-repo solver/agent downloads task attachments and
# writes OCR / extracted-image output into cwd (= repo root) during gaia runs.
# Root-anchored so a legitimately-tracked same-named file deeper in the tree is not
# hidden (the repo tracks zero root-level media). Deeper fix (follow-up): route the
# solver's attachment/OCR scratch to --user-files-root instead of cwd.
/ocr_pages/
/extracted_*/
/*.pdf
/*.png
